														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1247726">
									

<p>What are their nests made of? Wax, like with bees? &quot;Paper&quot;, like with wasps? Something else?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-779 is a species of insect similar in appearance to the common bee or a wasp.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'm no expert on bugs, but that image looks a lot more like a beetle than a bee or wasp.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-779 have been observed to operate at all times of the day, and are typically dismissed by residents as ordinary bees or wasps.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If I saw bee or wasp which was red and black I sure as heck would sit up and take notice.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>When injected with the venom, victims of SCP-779 will perceive SCP-779 as small humanoid figures with wings and believe that SCP-779 are assisting with the maintenance of the residence.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Does the venom also make the victims keep the &quot;fairies&quot; a secret? Since otherwise these people would end up telling their neighbors, and word would get around.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>As SCP-779 are voracious eaters, they will typically consume all food in the residence in a matter of days.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Insects which make nests/hives don't migrate every few days. Even if these were the exception, they'd have to have some way of carrying the eggs and grubs from one house to the next, since the queen is constantly laying eggs.</p>

