																		Browneys
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1472934"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1360611607 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Feb 2013 19:40</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1708230">
									

<p>So I saw the title of this article was &quot;Brownies&quot;, and I came here expecting something similar to &quot;orgasm muffins&quot;. The first thing I saw was a picture of a bug, and I was like, &quot;Wat?&quot; I read a little bit, and then I realized, &quot;Oh, like the <em>faery</em> - '<em>browney</em>', not &quot;<em>brownie</em>'.&quot;</p>
<p>I'm not sure how long it normally takes other people to get that…I wouldn't suggest fixing the name, though - &quot;Brownies&quot; <em>is</em> a name that draws people. That said, Browneys are supposed to love <em>honey</em>, not milk, I believe. I could be wrong, of course. :)</p>
<p>As for the rest…well, it's an explanation for an old mythical creature, <em>and</em> a cool bug SCP that doesn't eat you from the inside out - I like it. +1 :D</p>

							</div>

								
					
